external_knowledge:
- "Avid players" refers to users who are highly engaged in their preferred sport;
- "Logged more than 10 hours of playtime on average" means the user has an average of more than 10 hours of playtime across all sports;
- "Over 1000 miles in total distance" means the user has covered a total distance of more than 1000 miles across all activities.

- 'Top-rated' refers to the sports with the highest average ratings;
- 'Community shares' are instances where activities are shared in the community;
- 'Ratings' are values given by users to these shared activities, typically on a scale (e.g., 1-5 stars).

- "Highly rated users" refers to users with the highest average ratings;
- "Activity count" refers to the number of activity logs recorded for each user;
- "Total hours played" refers to the sum of hours spent on all activities by each user.

- 'Rated activities' refers to activities that have received at least one rating.;
- 'Weather outlook' refers to the general weather conditions such as 'Sunny', 'Rainy', or 'Overcast'.;
- 'Average rating' is the mean value of the ratings given to a share.

- 'Total hours played' refers to the sum of hours played across all activities;
- 'Average hours played' is the average hours spent per activity;
- 'Most common weather condition' is the weather condition that occurs most frequently during the user's activities.

- "blossoms are the most vibrant and frequent" refers to comments that have been made multiple times;
- "gardeners that tend to them more actively than the average keeper" refers to users who have more activities than the average number of activities across all users;
- "names of these gardeners" refers to the usernames of the users;
- "content of their most echoed remarks" refers to the content of the comments that have been made the most times.

- "Users with more than one favorite sport" refers to users who have listed more than one sport in their profile as a preferred activity;
- "Average duration they spend on these activities" is calculated by dividing the total hours played by the number of activities recorded for each user;
- "Ranked by the total hours played" means the results are sorted in descending order of the total hours played, with the most active users listed first.

- "favorite sport" refers to the sport that each user has played the most frequently;
- "embraced the most" indicates the sport with the highest count in their activity logs;
- "dedication" is measured by the average hours spent playing the sport.

- "stars of the community" refers to users with the highest engagement;
- "shining the brightest" refers to having the highest sum of unique comments and ratings;
- "top 5" means the five users with the highest engagement.
